SubjectCleaned: Why does pandas apply calculate twice
MainTextCleaned: In the current implementation apply calls func twice on the first column row to decide whether it can take a fast or slow code path This can lead to unexpected behavior if func has side effects as they will take effect twice for the first column row
Text: Why does pandas apply calculate twice In the current implementation apply calls func twice on the first column row to decide whether it can take a fast or slow code path This can lead to unexpected behavior if func has side effects as they will take effect twice for the first column row

SubjectCleaned: The POP3 and IMAP mail servers allow unencrypted logons
MainTextCleaned: The Postfix SMTP server and Cyrus IMAP POP3 server are not SSL enabled All of these protocols are clear text and any login to these servers requires that the username and password cross the network in plain text SANS Top 20 U5
